  - elementId: title
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 18, 1100, 38]
    content:
      style: "$actionTitle"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Structural Shift and Diminishing Returns Define H1 2026 Performance</p>
  - elementId: divider
    elementType: shape
    bounds: [60, 58, 1160, 1]
    shapeName: rect
    fill:
      type: solid
      color: "$border"
  - elementId: metric1
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 72, 265, 100]
    content:
      align: [left, top]
      lineHeight: 1.2
      text: |
        <p><span style="font-size:36px; color:$primary; font-family:Oranienbaum;">$835K</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:13px; color:$secondary;">H30 p50 Forecast</span></p>
  - elementId: metric2
    elementType: text
    bounds: [358, 72, 265, 100]
    content:
      align: [left, top]
      lineHeight: 1.2
      text: |
        <p><span style="font-size:36px; color:$primary; font-family:Oranienbaum;">32.9%</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:13px; color:$secondary;">Avg Coverage (p10–p90)</span></p>
  - elementId: metric3
    elementType: text
    bounds: [656, 72, 265, 100]
    content:
      align: [left, top]
      lineHeight: 1.2
      text: |
        <p><span style="font-size:36px; color:$primary; font-family:Oranienbaum;">11 / 42</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:13px; color:$secondary;">Well-Calibrated Grains</span></p>
  - elementId: metric4
    elementType: text
    bounds: [954, 72, 265, 100]
    content:
      align: [left, top]
      lineHeight: 1.2
      text: |
        <p><span style="font-size:36px; color:$primary; font-family:Oranienbaum;">118</span></p>
        <p><span style="font-size:13px; color:$secondary;">Anomalies Flagged</span></p>
  - elementId: insights
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 180, 1160, 500]
    content:
      fontSize: 18
      color: "$text"
      fontFamily: "Liter"
      lineHeight: 1.5
      align: [left, top]
      text: |
        <p><strong>1. Structural Shift Detected:</strong> Google Ads and Meta Ads show test-period means 2× higher than training means, indicating a Feb 2026 regime change. Model coverage is 0% for these grains at H60/H90, meaning the model is systematically underforecasting.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px"><strong>2. Search Remains Top Performer:</strong> Search campaigns show the highest ROAS (10.3x at H30 baseline) but with the steepest diminishing returns — increasing budget beyond 1.0x yields minimal incremental revenue.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px"><strong>3. Pmax Near Saturation:</strong> Pmax campaigns already operate at a low ROAS (1.3x at baseline) with $1,000/day spend, suggesting they are approaching diminishing returns even at current levels.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px"><strong>4. Organic Channels Stable:</strong> Organic_Search, Direct, and Email show no significant anomalies but also have zero spend, making them purely time-series dependent with no budget lever.</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px"><strong>5. Bing Ads Underutilized:</strong> Bing Ads has strong ROAS (6.3x at H30) but very low daily spend ($44), suggesting untapped potential for budget reallocation from saturated channels.</p>
  - elementId: source
    elementType: text
    bounds: [60, 692, 1100, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [left, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>Source: AIgnition Pipeline Stages 1–9, Data Period Jan 2024 – Jun 2026</p>
  - elementId: page-num
    elementType: text
    bounds: [1170, 692, 50, 18]
    content:
      style: "$caption"
      align: [right, middle]
      wrap: false
      text: |
        <p>03</p>
